This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the proposed method on public datasets suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a deep fully convolutional residual network suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
